import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].replace({1: 'Male', 2: 'Female'})
    sns.countplot(x='sex', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = data['age'].astype(int)
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].astype(int)
    data['sex'] = data['sex'].replace({1: 'male', 2: 'female'})
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', hue='sex', multiple='stack', kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of males and females in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['year']).sum().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    ax = sns.lineplot(x="year", y="people", data=data, color='blue')
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Population Density')
    plt.title('What is the population density in different years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
